# Deploy Convention

When a deploy is needed, always use `op-firebase-deploy` (global script on PATH).

## Commands

```bash
npm run deploy                 # full deploy (hosting + functions + rules + storage)
npm run deploy:hosting         # hosting only
npm run deploy:functions       # functions only
op-firebase-deploy --only hosting,functions  # any Firebase target combo
```

## How it works

- `op-firebase-deploy` reads ADC credentials from 1Password (`Private/GCP ADC/credential`)
- Auto-detects the Firebase project from `.firebaserc`
- Validates the ADC token before deploying (exchanges the refresh token with Google's token endpoint)
- If the token is stale, automatically opens `gcloud auth application-default login`, then updates 1Password with the fresh credential — no manual `op item edit` needed
- Writes credentials to a temp file (`umask 077`), sets `GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS`, runs `firebase deploy --non-interactive`, cleans up on exit
- Does not depend on `gcloud auth login` or `firebase login` sessions — only `GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS` is used
- Supports both `authorized_user` (user ADC) and `service_account` key types; service account keys skip validation since they never expire

## Token refresh

The script auto-detects and auto-refreshes stale tokens. No manual intervention is needed — if the token is expired, the script opens a browser for `gcloud auth application-default login` and updates 1Password automatically.

The ADC refresh token has no fixed expiry but is revoked on Google password change, explicit revocation, or 6 months of inactivity. A `firebase-deployer` service account exists in the project with deploy permissions; if the GCP org policy (`iam.disableServiceAccountKeyCreation`) is ever lifted, generate a key for it and store in 1Password for permanent non-interactive deploys.

To manually refresh the ADC (should not normally be needed):

```bash
gcloud auth application-default login --project=device-source-of-truth
op item edit "GCP ADC" --vault Private \
  "credential=$(cat ~/.config/gcloud/application_default_credentials.json)"
```

## Rules

- Never run `firebase deploy` or `npx firebase deploy` directly — always use `op-firebase-deploy` or `npm run deploy`
- Never run `firebase login` or `gcloud auth login` as part of a deploy flow
- Never store or print credentials; only use `op://` references in committed files
